%N A395322 Decimal expansion of the length of the longest edge of the polyhedron with 14 vertices with conjecturally maximum possible volume inscribed in the unit sphere.
%C A395322 Due to its dihedral symmetry of order 24, the polyhedron is completely determined by this length L. The 14 vertices are arranged as two vertices at the poles and two regular hexagons of vertices at a constant angular distance of 2*arcsin(L/2) = 63.70349895774623484573... degrees from the poles. L is the smallest positive root of the polynomial 9*x^4 - 288*x^2 + 768*x - 512.
%H A395322 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="https://www.randomwalk.de/sphere/volmax/pages/14.htm">Visualization of Polyhedron</a>, (1999).
%H A395322 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="https://www.randomwalk.de/sphere/volmax/videos/14c.mp4">Number of edges incident with the 14 vertices</a>, video (2021).
%H A395322 Hugo Pfoertner, <a href="/A395322/a395322.png">Visualization of the polyhedron with 14 vertices inscribed in the sphere</a>, (2021).
